2. The "Compliance Enhancements" (Medium Effort)
Document Versioning (Amendment Tracking): ISO 9001 requires strict tracking of document changes. If an Approved letter is found to have an error, the standard Frappe behavior is to "Cancel" and "Amend" it (creating QMS-OUT-2026-0001-1). We should add a "Reason for Amendment" mandatory text field that only appears when a document is amended, ensuring a clear audit trail.
Role-Based Dashboard: Create a custom "Workspace" (Dashboard) for the QMS User and QMS Executive. This would show metrics like "Pending Approvals", "Letters Dispatched This Week", and quick shortcuts to create new documents, rather than relying on the default Frappe lists.
Letter Templates (Text Blocks): Instead of typing out the body of the recommendation letter every time, we can create a Letter Template DocType. The user selects a template (e.g., "Tender Recommendation - Standard" or "Tender Recommendation - High Security"), and it automatically fills the standard paragraphs into the document body, leaving only specific variables (like dates or project names) to be filled out.
3. The "Power User Features" (Higher Effort)
Tender/Opportunity Integration: Deepen the connection with the CRM. If a letter is linked to an Opportunity, we can automatically pull the Opportunity value, expected close date, and specific requirements directly into a designated section of the letter.
Digital Signatures (Internal/Basic): While full PKI signatures are out of scope for the MVP, we can implement an internal signature feature. When the QMS Executive clicks "Approve", the system automatically appends a scanned image of their signature (stored securely in their User Profile) to the bottom of the generated PDF.